title: Amazon Basics Laptop Backpack Fits Up to 17-Inch Laptops, Black
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars roomy, easy to organise and long lasting.', 'author': 'Soso Ninidze', 'rating': 5, 'content': "have bought this Backpack i third time for me, advised also few of my friends and they also are very happy with this Backpack, for the price it is greatest bag which I had. material is good, zippers are great never failed for me, have big room and is good if you like orginizing backpack by each compartment for each theme of the day, for example I'm using 1 for my medications, 1 for cables, chargers and things like it and biggest compartment for laptop, documents, food and some extra clothes if needed. have good back as well, but if you carry extra have staff it can not distribute weight well enough. overall its is one of the best backpack for the price, roomy, easy to organise and long lasting.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 27, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Love it', 'author': 'L.K.C', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I run my backpacks through a lot and this one has continued to hold up. T holds a lot. The only thing I have to complain about is that the side clip straps broke ripped off pretty early on and the side mesh ripped pretty easy as well but I'd still buy again. The sippers and the rest of the backpack is super durable and even fully packed feels less heavy than other ones I've had. Recommended, especially if you're rough on backpacks.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States March 3, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Fits a 17.3" laptop quite snuggly, but...', 'author': 'JEH the Voice', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'The bag fits a 17.3" laptop quite snuggly, but it fits nonetheless. There is a considerable amount of space in each of the available sections, along several accessory pockets for those smaller items. The 2 mesh side pockets are big enough for a standard plastic water bottle, but not big enough for a nalgene water bottle.Taking it on a couple destinations so if there are any issues I find with it, I will edit my comments accordingly. As it stands now, good solid bag for the price and it does fit larger laptops.Update Feb 16, 2015:Been using this backpack on a daily basis while traveling to work and while traveling on business trips. Works great still! It has been the perfect companion bag and fits under the seat in front of you on an airplane so that it is easily accessible. If you are doing a one day trip or longer it has been very versatile on all occasions. I can have a couple days change of clothes with me and only have to carry on with me a suit, everything else is in the backpack. I may consider buying another for a B.O.B., still debating on something a bit more tactical otherwise. One last note, the grab handle on the top of the pack is extremely strong and can manage being yanked on regularly.If there are any major issues with the backpack I will note it later. You can buy this product with confidence.September 2015There are two recent flaws with the pack and not over excessive use either. The stitching for the water bottle holders are a bit weak and will eventually lose their attachment to the pack. Also, I was surprised to have one of the retention straps to fall off. The stitching is not as good as expected. I did not overload my bag, just nice and snug and one day if found the strap hanging on only by the clip. Still a nice design overall, but just a few discrepancies to be noted over time and general use. I don\'t want to speculate, but I will, this bag will have a good life expectancy in general use, but not if you think about a short B.O.B.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States July 8, 2014', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars The unabatingly impressive backpack that I didn't even realize I wanted", 'author': 'Adam', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I travel a lot for business and I used a laptop case to carry my files, receipts, laptop, chargers, etc. As an airline carry-on option, the laptop case was convenient because of its size, but it had one strap, and I was finding that my tendency to put it on my right shoulder over the years was causing my back to go a little out of whack, and switching sides constantly was not the solution I needed.This backpack was discounted a bit for Black Friday, and having seen the quality of AmazonBasics products before, I knew that $30 was a fair price and I expected a decent product based on the reviews. When it arrived, I was able to take everything from my laptop case - passport, flash drive, files, chargers and more - and transfer it into this backpack with ease. There are dedicated pockets that are intelligently sized (there is one small pocket that is flash-drive-shaped, which was amazing). And, because of the way it\'s constructed, it\'s smaller and lighter than my laptop case. From the beginning, I was impressed, but that was only the beginning.The backpack itself complies with my airline\'s (and, let\'s be reasonable, most airlines\') definition of a "personal item" rather than "carry-on luggage," whereas my laptop case was too wide to be considered a personal item (though most airlines wouldn\'t bug you, still, it\'s always better to be able to point to the regulation and say you\'re in the right!). This bag maximizes economy of space brilliantly, and fits under the seat in front of you on the plane, so no rummaging through the overhead compartments looking for your bag. I thought the bag couldn\'t get any better, but it didn\'t stop there.I was initially concerned about whether having a backpack rather than a laptop case would appear "unprofessional," but as a traveling salesperson, it didn\'t appear that anyone judged me for having a backpack rather than a case. The zippers are strong and large, so no cheap metal or plastic breaking on you as you try to open a zipper that got stuck on cloth. Everything is laid out very well. Having all my chargers, cables and files handy was useful during my presentations, when I was able to pull out hotspots, folders and other things with ease, and even keep my coins together for easy reach while paying tolls.I\'m excited to use this backpack for personal 1-2 day trips also, because I can definitely fit a bit of clothing in the other pocket I didn\'t use (there was so much space, I didn\'t need to!) and be able to travel in a plane, train or automobile without having to worry about lugging around...well, luggage. The side compartment is perfect for the average bottle of water, for people that want to use this backpack in the outdoors or for long trips, and just about any laptop will fit inside the slit in the back.If the events of Amazon\'s history as a company in the last two decades had only culminated in the design of this backpack, that would honestly be enough to justify its existence. Of course, I\'m exaggerating, but this backpack is yet another example among the many reasons more and more of my purchases are being made through Amazon. Their reputation for quality and economy of design understates the achievements of this backpack, which sets standards beyond all those previously achieved by Amazon.Thank you again, Amazon, and I look forward to seeing what the next item is that you decide to improve in ways I didn\'t even realize I wanted.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 14, 2015', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent budget-friendly backpack', 'author': 'Trevor', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Pros: Cheap, budget friendly A LOT of storage options Does not sag downwards like some other bags Still holding up very well after months of use Large laptop section fits multiple sizes of laptops comfortably, even my 15.5"Cons: Zips seem to be of not-so-good quality, prone to getting caught on inside seams and is sometimes difficult to operate Water bottle pouches are small, and require some shoehorning Laptop pouch offers nominal protection, not too bad, but could be betterAs you can see, the cons really aren\'t cons that one can\'t live with. I have had this backpack for months now, and I use it to transport books, computers, even clothes for a long weekend. It has held up well so far. I am especially appreciative of the fact that the base is well supported, meaning that if I had nothing really in the main compartments and a bunch of stuff in the outermost compartment, the backpack still maintains its shape and doesn\'t sag down too much, if at all, unlike certain cloth-bottomed backpacks.There are more storage compartments on this than a person will require, including 5 zippered compartments, (2 large, 1 sort of large, 1 medium and 1 small) the largest of which is internally divided into 3. It should be noted that the upper compartment on the front (as seen in the main product picture) actually extends all the way to the bottom. There are also 2 water bottle holders and a pen / iPod nano / earphone holder on the left strap.The straps are padded somewhat, and relatively comfortable, and I truly have no idea what functional purpose the clips have just above the water bottle holders on either side. They look good though, so I\'m not complaining. The water bottle holders are, however, a little small, so some fenangling may be required to stuff in a larger bottle. It is, however, very nice that there are two holders instead of the usual one.My only gripe with this bag are the zippers, which seem to be of relatively low quality. They do not zip or unzip smoothly, and are prone to getting caught on the inside seams. I am quite afraid that they will eventually split or break off, they truly do not inspire confidence.Overall, I absolutely enjoy this backpack and would recommend it to anyone looking for a budget-friendly backpack that can easily leave its more expensive cousins with a bloody nose. It also doesn\'t hurt that I much prefer the simpler design and I think it looks great.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States September 7, 2015', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars [Update1 06/27] Fits my 17.3" Dell Precision M6600 (Sort Of)', 'author': 'Farhan K', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'The media could not be loaded. Update 1 - 06/27 - Approximately one week after my purchase of this Backpack, I got an email from Amazon "Your purchase of the AmazonBasics Backpack for Laptops Up To 17-Inch comes with 6 months of FREE Unlimited Online Storage from Amazon Cloud Drive (a $29.99 value) " . Wow this was unexpected and a pleasant surprise as I did not read of this promotion anywhere in the description and it basically pays itself of the entire cost of the Backpack. I am not sure if this is a temporary or permanent promotion.Original Review : I purchased the AmazonBasics Backpack half expecting to return it as I was not entirely sure if it could fit my huge 17.3" Dell Precision M6600 Mobile workstation that I use for work . I mean this laptop is big, thick and heavy - It weighs in excess of 8 pounds and is measures 19.5" inches diagonal externally. But as you can see in my video that it has no issues swallowing my laptop with the least amount of shoehorning or protrusion - So I would declare this a fit , granted that the laptop will only fit in the main compartment outside the laptop sleeve. (see my video) Space, Build Quality & Comfort ------------------------------------------- The backpack has tons of space and compartments (almost too many for my requirements) to carry anything you can think of. I carry mainly my office laptop, powerbank, stationery , towels, lunchbox, headphones, documents and the occasional tablet in it daily with plenty of room to spare- The material of the backpack is fairly good for its price but its certainly not Jansport good.- With all the stuff I carry around my backpack weighs in excess of 12 pounds. Even with this heavy weight I find it comfortable to wear on my shoulders with no unnecessary stress or fatigue points on my body- The shoulder straps seem to be holding up to the 12 pound weight fairly well so far. I will update if that changes in the long run- As you can see it has no issues fitting my 17.3" Dell Precision M6600The Good------------------ Had loads of space and compartments to swallow anything you throw at it and is expandable further- Build quality is surprisingly good at this price point- Zippers glide smoothly- Good looking- Comfortable - Even weighing at 12 pounds after I put my stuff into it, I found it comfortable to wear on my shoulders. Its padded in the right placesThe Not So Good-------------------------- The only minor issue I found so far was an aesthetic one - Because its designed to be expandable and carry so much stuff - If you dont put a lot of things in it , the front part collapses and looks weird and squishy (see my video) . I wish that Amazon would have provided it a more rigid structure- Laptops greater than 17 inches will not fit in the laptop sleeve - They will only fit outside it in the main compartment.Overall I am very satisfied with my purchase and it is really a great value for money option which fulfills my need of fitting my large laptop ,have sufficient space to carry other stuff like my lunchbox, chargers and still be comfortable to wear', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States June 25, 2016', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars So pleased with this bag!', 'author': 'Jeffrey', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I bought this laptop backpack because I have been spending 3 days of my week in Coffee Shoppe’s while my husband is working. He doesn’t work well at home so each day I have been packing up a cloth grocery bag with snacks, bottled water, my laptop, my kindle ect and going with him to spend the day in different coffee shops around my city.Lugging all my stuff around on the bus in a cloth grocery back was so difficult and I had been looking for a good back pack that wasn’t too expensive, but still good quality and that had plenty of room for all the stuff I need and bring with me. After searching for a while and seeing that even normal Jansport backpacks that aren’t designed to carry laptops were $50 or more I was getting discouraged until I came across this Gem!This Bag carries 2 large laptops with a special area for both, has a holder for my water bottle, several individual pockets for things like my keys, medications, and snacks. It has a built in wallet type area that will fit cell phones, pens, pencils, small notebooks.Plus 2 or 3 outer pockets on the bag itself for smaller items.One of my biggest worries when looking to buy was that the laptop would be slamming against my back while I wore it. But this bag has plenty of cushioning between the back and where the laptop is stored.This bag would work for Students in place of a laptop case, or could easily be used for hikers or campers. It is versatile and has cushioning on the shoulder/arm pads and a handle for comfortable holding and wearing.The material seems strong and put together well.For the price on this product it is so worth it in my opinion. Normal Backpacks with way less storage can go for so much money and I was able to get this for $25.29!My only real disappointment was that there were no options to personalize it to my taste. I didn’t get a color choice like you do with most back packs or laptop cases. This is a black back pack with small areas of orange threads. While Orange is not my favorite it is subtle enough that I was okay with not having an option on color. Overall the bag appears like a normal back pack would, with an affordable price and a variety of pockets and holders on the bag that make up for the lack of color options!I am so pleased with this purchase and so glad I decided to get it!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States June 17, 2016', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '3.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy bag, cheap mesh pockets', 'author': 'NkW', 'rating': 3, 'content': 'The bag itself works well. It has a lot of room & several compartments for books, pencils, etc. the suddenness pockets have NOT held up. My son has had the bag 3 month & there are several large rips in the mesh rendering them not usable. This is disappointing because he has to bring a water bottle to school daily & the mesh pockets made for easy access. Tge mesh pockets in previous backpacks have lasted years. Maybe they just don’t make things like they used to.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 7, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and Spacious', 'author': 'Quintino machado', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'The structural abilities of this bag for the price is actually quite phenomenal.Currently in this photo there is a 15 inch laptop. One large 5 subject spiral. A happy planner. A laptop charger. 2 folders of paperwork. A pen bag with about 50 pens. 2 things of happy planner stickers. 1 text book. And an assortment of everyday small essentials like chapstick and glasses wipes.This bag actually makes those items feel fairly light on the back!The zippers are SUPER smooth. I’ve actually never had a backpack where I don’t have to fight with zippers. This one is wonderful for especially that feature!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 27, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Great product but water soluble, not water resistant', 'author': 'hobartfan', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I have been very happy with the quality of this product. Living in Southern California, I have not had much chance to take it out in wet weather, until today. Despite my using an umbrella, the contents of my pack got wet - all pockets, including the laptop pocket. Fortunately, I was able to get to shelter before my laptop was wet enough to suffer damage. I would recommend this product, but urge people to use a waterproof spray on it before going out into any kind of inclement weather.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}]

title: Amazon Basics Classic School Backpack - Black
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars As Much Detail as Possible', 'author': 'Jacob', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I've had this backpack from amazon for about a week so i'll just give my thoughts on this product. Prior to this back ive used a couple JanSport bags, and a Hiking bag.Ill try to get back with edits if anything changes.Pockets:Inside the main bag compartment there is a nice pocket that perfectly fits my 13 in Razer Blade Stealth inside a neoprene sleeve. This compartment is well padded, making me confident that my laptop will be protected from the contents in the main compartment.Right above that is a smaller zipper pocket that fits my laptop charger perfectly, This pocket is not padded.The main compartment has two more small open pockets, these are unpadded and have no zipper. This means that any of your items in this pocket can potentially fall out if you toss your bag around. I personally don't keep much in these pockets that can be damaged.The smaller compartment is nice and wide, usually i keep some small flash drives and my mouse in here. Again this is not padded so i don't put anything that can be damaged in here.Finally, on the outside of the bag you will get two side pockets with some velcro to keep them shut need be. I usually just throw an energy drink or bottled water on the go.Comfort:This bag has some pretty thin bag straps. This is fine for short durations, however for longer durations or with more things in my bag, it can start to get pretty uncomfortable quickly. I would have liked this bag to have slightly wider and softer straps. However for the price, this is not a bad trade-off.Aesthetic:This bag is plain. That is in no way an understatement. Its an all black bag with no accents or logo tags. When you open the bag, the inside has some light grey, which actually helps me find things on the bottom with less light.Price:If you need a bag that will do its job on the cheap then this is an amazing product. I personally have no issue saving some money and dealing with the shoulder straps. For the $12, this is the best price to performance bag i've personally used.Final Thoughts/Summary:The straps are a bit uncomfortable, however i would still get this over a JanSport for one main reason, this bag has some of the most useful pockets for in the main compartment for my needs. I would easily feel comfortable paying another $8 for this same bag and feel like i got a great deal. If you carry a good amount of heavy books then i would look for something with more padded shoulder straps, however if you are just moving from class to class, or in my case office to car to apartment, then i would wholeheartedly recommend this.Edit 1: I was wrong. There is a tag on the strap, its very discreet however i just cut mine off.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 9, 2016', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely Worth The Price', 'author': 'EJ', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I spent a lot of time looking for a very simple back pack to throw some spare work clothes in and eventually settled on this one. There isn't much to be said other than it is a simple backpack with a large front pocket and a more than reasonably sized main compartment. It is well constructed and the shoulder straps are well padded. I would say without a doubt it is worth the money. Heck even if it dies after a year of banging around in the work truck I will have long gotten my money's worth. Would buy again and am considering buying a spare in case they stop making these or crank the price up.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States October 21, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars One MILLION STARS.', 'author': 'Betty', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'If I could give this 1 million stars, I would. I am extremely particular about my backpack. My favorite backpack died a few months ago and I have been desperately seeking a good replacement. I cycle to and from work every day for 18 mi and have gone through about 6 amazon backpacks in the last 3 months. Like Goldilocks, I\'m 4\' 11" woman and size matters. 1 was too big (30 L), one was too small (15L barely carried my sneakers), some were too heavy (waterproof wet bag), some had too many stupid pockets (freeknight, who needs a helmet net??), one was super lightweight and a decent 20L but the straps aren\'t padded enough and cut into my shoulders when I had too much stuff in it (New Outlander). title: Della Gao Large Anti-Theft Laptop Backpack with USB Charging Port for 17-Inch Laptops
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive, but long lasting and durable!', 'author': 'Dr. Sean Henry', 'rating': 5, 'content': "This is my second Della Gao Travel Laptop Backpack, replacing an older identical one. And the only reason I am replacing the older one is because it is getting grungy and starting to stink after more than 2 years of daily use waking to work, often with a packed lunches inside. I probably could have washed it after detaching the USB charger, but at such a very reasonable price, I decided to get a new one just like it!I have used the backpack for traveling with my heavy 17-inch laptop, too. It is very sturdy and does not stretch the stitches apart at the shoulder straps like another brand of laptop backpack I once had. The back of the outermost laptop compartment is well padded, which protects the laptop and also makes the backpack more comfortable to wear. I have not had the opportunity to use the USB charging port, but I'm glad it's there, just in case.I really like the mesh outer pockets on both sides of the backpack for my keys and smartphone when I'm walking (I walk in a low crime area). The pockets would be good for a water bottle or small thermos, too. The red and white tabs on the backpack are highly reflective for safety after dark. It's water resistance keeps things dry when I am walking in the rain.I've had many backpacks over the years, and except for an expensive leather backpack I had back in the 1990s, this Della Gao Travel Laptop Backpack is my favorite!", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States November 10, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great product', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'All the pockets are easy to access and tons of storage space.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great for. International trip', 'author': 'patricia l. smith', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'My husband loved it. Great under seat bag. Put his camera equipment and fit good on shoulders and waterproof for light snow and rain. Pack overnight clothes when we traveled short trip.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 26, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Quality Bag', 'author': 'Collin LeBlanc', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'This is actually better than I expected it to be. I thought that maybe because it wasn\'t a name brand or an American company it might come with lower quality, as tends to be the case, but it is actually a really nice bag! It has more than enough space for my laptop and allows me to hold a binder, a notebook, an agenda, cords for my computer, two power banks, and lots of water without it feeling like it is packed to the brim. Everything seems comfortable so far, and I\'m enjoying it! As for the "security" rating though, I rate it a 2 star just because the lock is hard to set up and seems cheap. The instructions for the lock were clearly put into google translate as indicated by the grammar which hardly makes sense. The lock was overall trash, and I had to throw it away. That isn\'t really a big con to me, so I gave this product a 4 star because in every other way I\'m satisfied so far :)', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States September 18, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Fits MacBook Pro 15 + sleeve, lots of room for more stuff, good for day-to-day travel, air carry-on.', 'author': 'the kat', 'rating': 5, 'content': '15.6", PURPLEi JUST received this, so this is based on first impressions:TLDR:If i need to replace due to anything other than catastrophic failure, i would get this again.Paid: $29.99 USD. Free Shipping (Amazon Prime). Received in two days.Easily holds MBP 15" with a protective sleeve, plus several notebooks (paper or digital) and/or binders, charger(s), a light-weight jacket or sweater, miscellaneous small personal stuff, orthe computer/notebook, charger(s), overnight change of clothes, a small makeup bag,Good for day-to-day commuter use, or as personal item or carry-on for air travel.Worth the price (so far).OVERALL:i wouldnʻt ask this to protect a laptop from a 5-6ʻ fall off your shoulder onto a hard surface, like just dropping the backpack onto a hard floor - if the computer survived more than a couple of times, iʻd consider the aluminum-silicon gods being extra generous. However, if you fell off your bike while wearing it, and you absorbed part of the fall, i think your laptop and backpack might come out ok. (yeah, iʻve gone through that before, donʻt want to test this back pack with that, though.) Good capacity and access. Construction should stand up to light-moderate use (up to 8-10 lb).DETAILS:Outer shell:medium duty polyester knit fabric: the manufacturer/vendor answering a question says it is 900 denier; not outback trekking material, but good enough for around-town commuter use. reported as water resistant, feels like it, but i donʻt plan to deliberately test it just yet. The front, bottom, and back outer shell is lined with a thin padding that feels like maybe 1/8" poly-something, the kind of material used for wrapping light-weight things for packing, The back of the pack has an additional foam padding, not super thick, adds a bit of protection for contents, but possibly more for providing wearer comfort. Construction feels adequate for carrying a computer and a few light things (notebooks, jacket, etc.) up to about 8-10 lbs to me.Interior lining:medium-light weight polyester. The entire backpack is lined and divided with this material. Feels as though it too might be water resistant, although, again, iʻm not testing it.zippers: medium duty(?) nylon. one very light-duty combination padlock included.shoulder straps: 2 1/4" wide seam-to-seam, padding 2" wide.hand strap (top): 7 1ʻ2" long, 1" wide, 3/8" thick (thick medium dense material core, like urethane foam?)luggage cart strap: on the back surface of the backpack, allows it to be plunked onto the top of rolling luggage by the rolling luggage handle, and prevented from falling off.reflector tabs: 1/2" x 3/4" (4x), 1" x 3/4" (1x)Side Pockets: 6" deep, 4 3/4" wide, 3/8" wide elastic cuff expands from 5" to ~7". Synthetic (Poly or Nylon?) mesh, 3/8" elastic opening cuff. Holds a 3 1/4" wide water bottleMain cargo section:interior dimensions:5 3/4" deep at base, tapering to 3 1/12" at top.12" wide at base, a mild taper to 11 3/4" at the top of the laptop pocket, and the last 1 1/4" of height tapers from 10 1/2" to 7" width.17 3/4ʻ tall.Lots of room for laptop, and a two inch 3-ring binder, or one or two textbooks, notebooks, etc. Someone in the questions section of the reviews said this can hold a 5" binder: it probably could hold a laptop and that,, but i suspect not much else. Maybe the 17" or the 18.4" models have deeper capacity.laptop pocket is a 1" deep bellows- or safari style pocket, so it isnʻt stretched to accomodate even my MacBook Pro 15ʻ Unibody in padded sleeve. The pocket is 12" tall, so the entire laptop fits in the pocket. The inner-facing side of the pocket is lightly padded, so it will last longer, and protect the computer somewhat from scratching or denting by any hard objects you might have in the main cargo section of the backpack.Pass through for USB and headphone cables. Pass-through is NOT watertight! rubber strain relief around the holes in the fabric, but no rain deflector like on the larger model of backpack. moisture can get in, depending on how heavy the rain or spill is.Secondary section:interior dimensions1 7/8" deep at base, tapering to 1 1/4" at top11" wide at base, tapering to 9" near the top15" tall at the zipperpatch pockets, main one is 5" deep, 9" height to zipper, sewn onto divider wall between secondary compartment and main cargo compartment.Organizer compartment11" at base, tapering to 9" at top15" tallzipper opening reaches to 10" height.flat profileEssentially, a patch pocket with a zipper opening, the front surface is the padded/lined shell, the inner side the same interior lining as everything else.three patch-style credit card-sized RFID pockets. not tested for effectiveness yet.Should be able to tuck a notebook in this space, but probably not anything wider than a 3/4" 3-ring binder, unless you donʻt mind swiping volume from the other compartments.WHAT I LIKE:PROTECTION:MOST of the the outer shell is padded (albeit lightly). It should protect from casual bumps agains desks, shelves, etc.CAPACITY:The shell feels like it will stand up to day-to-day light-to medium duty use. Construction is adequate for carrying about 10-12 pounds. More than that would probably start to strain seams, handles, and zippers.LOTS of capacity for a 15" laptop (even the MacBook Pro Unibody) in a foam sleeve, plus charger, note pads (paper or digital), one or two medium to large books, a light jacket.For air travel, I can probably squeeze my purse inside and use the back pack as my "personal item". Even stuffed to capacity, this probably will fit under most airline seats.ACCESSIBILITY:The Main and Secondary compartments have wide openings: the Main compartment opens 12" from the top on both sides (double zipper), the Secondary opens 8" from the top, also double zipper. The front organizer pocket easily holds my iPad 2021 in its sleeve, so pulling it out at airport security is no problem. Depending on how much stuff i have packed, the laptop should easily come out and go back into its pocket as well.ORGANIZATION:Each of the compartments (Main, Secondary, Organizer) is large enough to accommodate a notebook/notepad. Organizing paper documents is much easier with this rather than a single compartment or with small compartments.oh yeah, the PURPLE is awesome.WHAT I WISH:MORE PADDING:The sides and top of the backpack are not padded - just the outer shell and inner lining. I wish these were padded, to help cushion falls/drops/bumps. iʻm kind of klutzy at times, and so every bit of protection helps.The separations between compartments are made of the interior lining fabric only; i wish these were also padded, as they would add protection and also give more body to the Secondary and Organizer compartments.The shoulder straps have thin padding (1/8"?): because they are 2" wide, it should mitigate the cutting into my shoulders, but i tend to overload my backpack, so extra padding is always welcome.STRONGER ZIPPERS: the bane of my existence. i hope these zippers last the two years i want to get out of this backpack. not super confident, but if i donʻt overload it, i might make it.BIGGER/DEEPER SIDE POCKET with drawstring closure: i carry 3 1/4" dia. 1 liter bottles with insulation; the side pockets just fit them, without insulating pouch, while they do fit, the 6" depth and elastic cuff seem a bit limited for larger water bottles. I guess itʻs a trade-off, since the pockets are just deep enough so that they donʻt interfere with the main compartment zippers.Cord Passthrough unnecessary: for me, putting holes in a backpack doesnʻt make sense - itʻs just somewhere for moisture to get in. Great amount of pockets inside and the bag is very comfortable and very durable from rough treatment.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 9, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Almost perfect but no laptop cushioning', 'author': 'Ed.Doc99', 'rating': 4, 'content': "This backpack is GREAT!! I got it for its dimensions for an international travel carryon to maximize cubic inches (AerLingus, to be exact).I stuffed it full, and along with my medium sized Lug bag, I could’ve gone full carryon/no checked baggage if I’d been just a bit more disciplined because they’re really is a TON of room in this backpack.My only complaints are:1. The laptop storage area, while ample and well-designed in that it has a wide elastic strap with Velcro at the end, has ZERO padding between the laptop and the exterior or bottom of the backpack. Not a problem while you’re wearing it, but *very* concerning if you’re stowing this in overhead bins on airplanes or public transit with your precious laptop inside. **So you’ll want to get a very protective laptop sleeve to use inside this backpack.**3. No anti-theft technology other than double zippers that have holes large enough to accept luggage locks. I did get TSA-approved combination locks elsewhere on Amazon, and they’ve been great.4. The chest strap is bizarre because it’s not long enough to go across an adult human’s chest. It’s only about seven inches long. That’s confusing. Maybe I’m misunderstanding something there.The clamshell feature for the electronics area *might* be pointless because the backpack is so tall. I say “might” because perhaps you’ll have a more favorable experience than mine, below:AerLingus, as of July 2023, does not have a contract with TSA 🤔, so I couldn’t use my KTN to get through security faster. 🤯 🤷\u200d♀️ Thus, I had to put this backpack in a security bin and remove my laptop, portable monitor, and Kindle.I asked if I could just unzip it all the way and lie it flat Like a clamshell, but the security agent kindly pointed out that when opened all the way, this backpack extends beyond the boundaries of the (quite large) security bin, so he said I indeed had to remove all my electronics.I don’t know if every agent would've said that, but that was my experience this time.I do understand that to include the upgrades listed here that I’d like to see, it would cost a lot more for this backpack. I haven't experienced any rips or tears during my use, and I expect this backpack to last for a long time.Overall Impression:The Lenovo Laptop Backpack B210 is a solid choice for tech enthusiasts like myself who value both style and functionality. It's lightweight, comfortable to carry, and offers ample storage for everyday essentials. The water-resistant fabric and durable construction provide peace of mind, and the clean design makes it suitable for various settings. For the price, it's a great value proposition, and I would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a reliable and stylish backpack for their tech gear.-Value: I believe the B210 offers good value for its price point. It's not the cheapest backpack on the market, but the quality and features justify the cost.-Durability: Based on my initial impressions and the quality of materials, I expect this backpack to be durable and long-lasting.-Usability: The B210 is easy to use and navigate, with well-organized compartments and comfortable carrying straps.-Innovation: While not groundbreaking, the backpack incorporates thoughtful features like water-resistant fabric and a padded laptop compartment, making it a practical choice for tech users.-Overall: I would recommend the Lenovo Laptop Backpack B210 to anyone looking for a stylish, functional, and durable backpack for their everyday tech essentials.I hope this review is helpful! Please let me know if you have any questions.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 2, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars For the price, excellent choice!', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Worth the money. I\'ve been using this bag about a month now on daily subway travel, and while I\'m happy with it, I know it probably won\'t be a have-it-forever bag, which is fine by me. I\'ve never had a subway commute before, so I just wanted to get a sense of whether I liked using a backpack or whether I needed to invest in a better shoulder bag, and for that, this fits the bill.I\'m a woman of fairly small stature, 5\'2 and petite all around, so I didn\'t want to feel like I was back in my middle school days with a backpack that made me look like an ersatz turtle clomping down the street. I wanted something fairly professional, slim, and with a little bit of something, not just another black backpack. And obviously, for a trial run, I didn\'t want to spend a lot.This bag in the blue color fit the bill. It\'s a very nice neutral blue, like a pair of jeans, so it goes with nearly everything. It doesn\'t appear to be showing dirt or grime yet, which is nice. The zippers are fairly high quality considering; I haven\'t had any issues with them sticking or getting jammed. The fabric appears to be a decent quality nylon and is fairly water resistant. I wouldn\'t call it waterproof, nor would I trust my computer in there in a heavy rainstorm without an umbrella or putting it under a jacket, but for a drizzle or minor shower everything inside has stayed dry.The lining is cheap nylon. Full stop. It will tear in time. But it\'s nicely designed, with an integrated front pocket big enough for a large-ish smart phone, car keys, metro card, chapstick, and a few other sundries without a problem. It\'s a deep pocket with a shallower "shelf" pocket, which is nice to keep the smaller things accessible. The main compartment is roomier than you\'d think, even with a 15 inch laptop inside. The laptop compartment is not very well padded, kind of not padded at all almost, but it\'s roomy. There are also two smaller pockets along the front of the main compartment, big enough for a cell phone, pens, that sort of stuff. And then the deep well easily fits a small umbrella, a Tupperware for lunch, a large-ish water bottle, and a large wallet, even with a laptop inside. I can also cram a packable rain jacket in there without trouble, though it starts to look kind of stuffed at that point.Don\'t labor under any delusions that this thing is going to magically distribute weight or anything like that. It won\'t. You are carrying your load on your shoulders. It\'s not super well padded, it\'s not super breathable. If you\'re looking for a bag that\'s going to be at your side 24/7 around the country or around the world, and be waterproof and super protective of all your stuff and be near weightless on your back and have 7000 pockets for all your little odds and ends, this ain\'t it. My husband is appalled at this bag, because his backpack has those 7000 dedicated pockets for odds and ends and he can\'t fathom life without that level of organization. And maybe my "forever bag" will have that. But for a cheap backpack for once in a while use, or the casual commuter, or someone who just wants to feel out using a backpack as a work bag rather than a more traditional shoulder bag, this is a great buy.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States November 18, 2019', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Second Purchase', 'author': 'Adolph Dixon', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I purchase this backpack almost two years ago. title: ULANZI BP10 Hardshell Camera Backpack, Professional Waterproof Photography Camera Case Anti Theft Travel for Photographers Unisex Drone DSLR Mirrorless Camera Lens Tripod Holder 17'' Laptop Black 35L
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Finally! An affordable quality bag for my gear!', 'author': 'Christopher', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I\'ve been looking for a bag that\'s not ridiculously overpriced, that\'s durable, and has room for more gear than I usually carry. I\'m easily able to fit a 5D Mark IV with a 70-200 2.8 II attached, a 6D Mark II with a 24-70 2.8 II attached, a 100mm 2.8 L Macro, a 50mm 1.8, 24-105 F4 II, 35mm 1.4 II, 16-35mm F4 inside, and my Godox V860 III fits in the front pouch with room to spare. I haven\'t even expanded the bag to gain its additional 10L of space, but that\'ll come in handy for traveling when I need to pack clothes and other essentials. There are also a ton of pockets for memory cards, card readers, batteries, etc. All for under $150 USD. The outer materials of the bag are soft but durable, and the fabrics inside are all soft to the touch but well made. The velcro tabs are also easy to configure how I need them, and I still have a couple of pieces left over. The belt attachment that comes with the bag fits me, even though I\'m a big guy (6\'4" and 365lbs).I don\'t often travel with this much gear, but I have an out of state wedding I\'m going to be photographing in April and I needed a bag that fits extra gear, and can be taken as a carry on. Overall, VERY impressed with this new bag. This is also my first purchase of a Ulanzi product, so I\'ll have to check some of their other stuff out now as well. With everything I have loaded so far, the total weight of the bag is at 22.7 lbs.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 31, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Everything but the kitchen sink fits.', 'author': 'gail duckworth', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'In preparation for an African Safari coming up in June, I found myself in need of a larger camera backpack. After many hours spent researching what was out there, I settled on the Ulanzi bp10 hardshell camera backpack 35l. It seems to be very well made, has plenty of room for all my gear, is comfortable on my back, and most importantly there is a zippered access panel on both sides. Although I have only had this backpack for a week, as of right now, I have no complaints and would definitely recommend it.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '2.0 out of 5 stars Zippers do not hold up', 'author': 'Jordan Johnson', 'rating': 2, 'content': 'Zippers are not built to last. Coming from a langly bag that has very sturdy zippers I was shocked. You will be replacing them in 2 years be warned!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': False}, {'title': "4.0 out of 5 stars It's a very well designed bag but has a flaw I don't think it will last years of hard use.", 'author': 'Jimmy Ji', 'rating': 4, 'content': "This bag is hard to fully recommend, but I don't think it's a bad bag.I love the look and design and all the compartments and pockets are amazing.It uses it's space really well and has more pockets than most other bags if that is important to you.The expansion from 25l to 35l is cool but also a problem since you sacrifice that extra 10l as a separate compartment instead of in the main compartment. So the depth of where you will put your camera and lenses could be deeper if it wasn't split into 2 compartments but you actually don't have that much as you would think. I am using small/medium lenses in my photos. Something like a 24-105 would not be flush with the main compartment. (But you could still zip it up)I thought I could live with the PU leather, but if you are like me and throw your bag around then I do not think the material will last.What I hate the most about this bag is that you have to open it face down backup so that means the front is on whatever the ground surface is. I wish there was at least another hard cover on the other front pouch to take the damage and force , but since there isn't I can see the front bottom pouch getting shredded over time.Also the fact you have to open the main compartment with the front down mean you have to keep zipping it up to then flip back around to get to the front pockets. This bag slowed me down on a recent shoot a lotlIf you swing the backpack around to the front to grab the camera on one of the side zippers that go to the main compartment the camera will be upside down because of that reason that it has to open face down.I love the included waist strap that you can attach or take off. I had to tuck the clip straps underneath the pockets since I did not want it dangling and honestly it works great. Not sure if it was designed for that.I can recommend this if you don't think you will abuse your backpack, but I am so run and gun the backpack will get pushed to it's limits though I think $150 is a bit high.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 20, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': 'se ve muy bien', 'author': 'javier', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'apenas la usare pero se ve de muy buena calidad, estaba buscanbdo una mochila asi desde hace tiempo y otras de 2500 o menos se rompian facil por el peso que cargo en la mochila pero esta s eve que resistira mucho y es muy amplia', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in Mexico January 5, 2024', 'is_verified': True}]

reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Always use a product for 30 days before I review.', 'author': 'Kristina', 'rating': 5, 'content': "The media could not be loaded. I even returned two prior to finding this one. I carry a back pack every where with me, that's why I'm so anal when it comes to selection. This one arches back a bit which allows it to actually open up when it's unzipped. I think that's also why it hasnt bent a single notebook, file, binder, etc.The front zipper pocket is amazingly deep and surprisingly it doesn't look bulky when I'm in a hurry and just shove 50 things inside of it.The zippers haven't given me a single issue, which is impressive.My son accidentally knocked a cup of juice off the table and all over it... I carry my Samsung tablet inside one of the pockets in the main pouch.. well I kid you not when i say that the inside of this bag never got wet. Yes it was zipped up but the juice was all over the bag! The front, top, sides, down the back and the straps. Cleaning juice off this bag was a fricken breeze y'all! I didnt have to run it through the washer, nor dryer. Just a quick wipe down with a wet rag and dabbed it with a dry one... still looks and feels brand new. The quality alone is worth the money. Soft, silky material. Again, no issues with any zipper and the bag itself is surprisingly much larger then i had expected.The only con with this bag is in the name. title: Amazon Basics Classic School Backpack - Black
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars As Much Detail as Possible', 'author': 'Jacob', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I've had this backpack from amazon for about a week so i'll just give my thoughts on this product. Prior to this back ive used a couple JanSport bags, and a Hiking bag.Ill try to get back with edits if anything changes.Pockets:Inside the main bag compartment there is a nice pocket that perfectly fits my 13 in Razer Blade Stealth inside a neoprene sleeve. This compartment is well padded, making me confident that my laptop will be protected from the contents in the main compartment.Right above that is a smaller zipper pocket that fits my laptop charger perfectly, This pocket is not padded.The main compartment has two more small open pockets, these are unpadded and have no zipper. This means that any of your items in this pocket can potentially fall out if you toss your bag around. I personally don't keep much in these pockets that can be damaged.The smaller compartment is nice and wide, usually i keep some small flash drives and my mouse in here. Again this is not padded so i don't put anything that can be damaged in here.Finally, on the outside of the bag you will get two side pockets with some velcro to keep them shut need be. I usually just throw an energy drink or bottled water on the go.Comfort:This bag has some pretty thin bag straps. This is fine for short durations, however for longer durations or with more things in my bag, it can start to get pretty uncomfortable quickly. I would have liked this bag to have slightly wider and softer straps. However for the price, this is not a bad trade-off.Aesthetic:This bag is plain. That is in no way an understatement. Its an all black bag with no accents or logo tags. When you open the bag, the inside has some light grey, which actually helps me find things on the bottom with less light.Price:If you need a bag that will do its job on the cheap then this is an amazing product. I personally have no issue saving some money and dealing with the shoulder straps. For the $12, this is the best price to performance bag i've personally used.Final Thoughts/Summary:The straps are a bit uncomfortable, however i would still get this over a JanSport for one main reason, this bag has some of the most useful pockets for in the main compartment for my needs. I would easily feel comfortable paying another $8 for this same bag and feel like i got a great deal. If you carry a good amount of heavy books then i would look for something with more padded shoulder straps, however if you are just moving from class to class, or in my case office to car to apartment, then i would wholeheartedly recommend this.Edit 1: I was wrong. There is a tag on the strap, its very discreet however i just cut mine off.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 9, 2016', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely Worth The Price', 'author': 'EJ', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I spent a lot of time looking for a very simple back pack to throw some spare work clothes in and eventually settled on this one. It is well constructed and the shoulder straps are well padded. I would say without a doubt it is worth the money. Heck even if it dies after a year of banging around in the work truck I will have long gotten my money's worth. Would buy again and am considering buying a spare in case they stop making these or crank the price up.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States October 21, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars One MILLION STARS.', 'author': 'Betty', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'If I could give this 1 million stars, I would. I am extremely particular about my backpack. My favorite backpack died a few months ago and I have been desperately seeking a good replacement. I cycle to and from work every day for 18 mi and have gone through about 6 amazon backpacks in the last 3 months. Like Goldilocks, I\'m 4\' 11" woman and size matters. 1 was too big (30 L), one was too small (15L barely carried my sneakers), some were too heavy (waterproof wet bag), some had too many stupid pockets (freeknight, who needs a helmet net??), one was super lightweight and a decent 20L but the straps aren\'t padded enough and cut into my shoulders when I had too much stuff in it (New Outlander). But this Amazon Basics one is just right. It\'s so simple really. Roomy, good depth and width, carries all of my gym clothes, shoes, laptop and room to spare, padded inside pocket, small zippered internal pocket for important stuff, huge front pocket for random stuff, 2 sizeable side pockets for easy access to key/cards/cell phone with velcro to close (genius)! So few backpacks have velcro on the side pockets. It\'s either wide open and easy for stuff to fall out, or zippered which makes it not-so-easy to access. The color is SOOOO pretty! I love this vibrant baby blue!! It\'s so comfortable to bike with it!! I put it on and it felt just right!!! Seriously, for $15, I want to get 10 of them in every color and store them in the basement, just in case they get discontinued in 2020. I want to buy one for all my friends and family members. I want to wear it out on a hot date. I want to... oh you get the picture. Construction looks great and hopefully it lasts a year. I sprayed the entire backpack with Granger\'s waterproofing spray and tested it in the shower and water rolls right off of it. Now it\'s an even awesomer water-resistant backpack. Couldn\'t be happier. Wish I didn\'t spend over $100 on all the other backpacks that I will now be giving away. title: ULANZI BP10 Hardshell Camera Backpack, Professional Waterproof Photography Camera Case Anti Theft Travel for Photographers Unisex Drone DSLR Mirrorless Camera Lens Tripod Holder 17'' Laptop Black 35L
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Finally! An affordable quality bag for my gear!', 'author': 'Christopher', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I\'ve been looking for a bag that\'s not ridiculously overpriced, that\'s durable, and has room for more gear than I usually carry. I\'m easily able to fit a 5D Mark IV with a 70-200 2.8 II attached, a 6D Mark II with a 24-70 2.8 II attached, a 100mm 2.8 L Macro, a 50mm 1.8, 24-105 F4 II, 35mm 1.4 II, 16-35mm F4 inside, and my Godox V860 III fits in the front pouch with room to spare. I haven\'t even expanded the bag to gain its additional 10L of space, but that\'ll come in handy for traveling when I need to pack clothes and other essentials. There are also a ton of pockets for memory cards, card readers, batteries, etc. All for under $150 USD. The outer materials of the bag are soft but durable, and the fabrics inside are all soft to the touch but well made. The velcro tabs are also easy to configure how I need them, and I still have a couple of pieces left over. The belt attachment that comes with the bag fits me, even though I\'m a big guy (6\'4" and 365lbs).I don\'t often travel with this much gear, but I have an out of state wedding I\'m going to be photographing in April and I needed a bag that fits extra gear, and can be taken as a carry on. Overall, VERY impressed with this new bag. This is also my first purchase of a Ulanzi product, so I\'ll have to check some of their other stuff out now as well. With everything I have loaded so far, the total weight of the bag is at 22.7 lbs.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 31, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Everything but the kitchen sink fits.', 'author': 'gail duckworth', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'In preparation for an African Safari coming up in June, I found myself in need of a larger camera backpack. It seems to be very well made, has plenty of room for all my gear, is comfortable on my back, and most importantly there is a zippered access panel on both sides. Although I have only had this backpack for a week, as of right now, I have no complaints and would definitely recommend it.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '2.0 out of 5 stars Zippers do not hold up', 'author': 'Jordan Johnson', 'rating': 2, 'content': 'Zippers are not built to last. Coming from a langly bag that has very sturdy zippers I was shocked. You will be replacing them in 2 years be warned!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': False}, {'title': "4.0 out of 5 stars It's a very well designed bag but has a flaw I don't think it will last years of hard use.", 'author': 'Jimmy Ji', 'rating': 4, 'content': "This bag is hard to fully recommend, but I don't think it's a bad bag.I love the look and design and all the compartments and pockets are amazing.It uses it's space really well and has more pockets than most other bags if that is important to you.The expansion from 25l to 35l is cool but also a problem since you sacrifice that extra 10l as a separate compartment instead of in the main compartment. So the depth of where you will put your camera and lenses could be deeper if it wasn't split into 2 compartments but you actually don't have that much as you would think. I am using small/medium lenses in my photos. Something like a 24-105 would not be flush with the main compartment. (But you could still zip it up)I thought I could live with the PU leather, but if you are like me and throw your bag around then I do not think the material will last.What I hate the most about this bag is that you have to open it face down backup so that means the front is on whatever the ground surface is. I wish there was at least another hard cover on the other front pouch to take the damage and force , but since there isn't I can see the front bottom pouch getting shredded over time.Also the fact you have to open the main compartment with the front down mean you have to keep zipping it up to then flip back around to get to the front pockets. This bag slowed me down on a recent shoot a lotlIf you swing the backpack around to the front to grab the camera on one of the side zippers that go to the main compartment the camera will be upside down because of that reason that it has to open face down.I love the included waist strap that you can attach or take off. I had to tuck the clip straps underneath the pockets since I did not want it dangling and honestly it works great. Not sure if it was designed for that.I can recommend this if you don't think you will abuse your backpack, but I am so run and gun the backpack will get pushed to it's limits though I think $150 is a bit high.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 20, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': 'se ve muy bien', 'author': 'javier', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'apenas la usare pero se ve de muy buena calidad, estaba buscanbdo una mochila asi desde hace tiempo y otras de 2500 o menos se rompian facil por el peso que cargo en la mochila pero esta s eve que resistira mucho y es muy amplia', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in Mexico January 5, 2024', 'is_verified': True}]

title: LOVEVOOK Laptop Backpack for Women Work Travel Backpack Purse Commuter Business Computer Bag Teacher Doctor Nurse Bags, College Backpack Daypack with USB Charging Port, 15.6 Inch, Black-brown
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, stain resistant, fits all my stuff. 👍', 'author': 'Kate', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I am a student in photography and art. I’m also disabled and chronically ill. Ergo, my bag has to carry a LOT of stuff — spare masks, medication, powdered electrolytes, camera lenses, water bottles, snacks, textbooks, art supplies, noise canceling headphones, spare film, DnD stuff, and other items. Sometimes my folding cane as well. So I wanted a school bag that didn’t feel like a freshman backpack that could store the kitchen sink.I ended up ordering two bags, one of these and one from a different brand. Despite being a little cheaper than the other brand, the quality is MUCH higher on this bag. I love it. It’s incredibly sturdy and stain resistant (getting it in navy blue didn’t hurt in that regard). There’s a gazillion pockets so everything has a home. I use the little zipper bag for little odds and ends I need easy access to like Liquid IV, emergency meds, antibacterial wipes, microfibers, etc. In spite of everything I shove in there, there’s still enough room for my binders, textbooks, laptop, etc. When I’m all loaded down and carrying on both shoulders, the weight distribution is comfortable and even, and it doesn’t interfere with me using my cane.It’s also just a beautiful bag. I really like the design choices. There’s an internal bar in the top of the backpack underneath the zipper to help keep its form. It opens like a coin purse and makes loading and unloading very easy. The details are well designed and implemented. I think others have had zipper issues but I have not.The big front flap does not have a zipper. It’s just the flap down holding it in place. I imagine it would be very easy for someone to reach in and steal from you. I am not in crowds or other environments that invite pickpockets, so this isn’t an issue for me. Also there’s a zippered pocket under the straps (protected by your back when you’re carrying it) for cash/cards, but I think it would be very uncomfortable to carry your entire wallet in there.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States October 7, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars The Bag Is Amazing -- The Clutch, not so much', 'author': 'Emma', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'This bag is better than the product photos... Legit, gorgeous product. Mine came packaged in a bag with a little luxury-kind of drawstring bag. It was cute!As a smaller woman (I\'m 5\'1") this backpack is the perfect size for my back. It doesn\'t feel bulky or look comically large on me. The fabric combination feels pretty good, no complaints there. It has a ton of pockets.... I don\'t know why I need this many pockets but hopefully it prevents the graveyard of junk that ends up at the bottom of all my bags. One fun pocket is right where the bag rests against your back (probably a great spot for a wallet or valuable stuff when traveling so you dont have someone stealing stuff). Great security feature.This would easily fit a 15" laptop. In the picture I have my 13" macbook pro in the back pocket (still has room to move it around) and my 6.8" kindle signature in the next pocket. This is going to be my teacher school year bag....! Later on, I will update with how durable it is. At work, I have a 15 inch Dell so I will test that some other time.I like how there is no flip top over the top of the bag to make access easier. I had a similar bag to this that I always struggled with the flip top to access items inside.The small clutch that comes with it is the only thing I really don\'t care for -- It might be good for a small makeup holder, maybe a first aid kit/feminine hygiene kit, potentially diabetic supplies; but, in comparison to the bag, it\'s just feels like an after thought. It\'s not as nice looking or feeling. I don\'t like the mesh and elastic bands. I think the zipper pull on it is pretty though, it compliments the bag. I think it\'s fine as a little freebie kind of thing but it\'s not anything AMAZING.Please note: I am an Amazon Vine Reviewer but I was not sponsored to review this item 😊.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 12, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars It's perfect for travel", 'author': 'J. M. C.', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I ordered the black and gray bag, and it's gorgeous. The striped lining is super cute too, and makes finding things inside much easier than if it were a dark color.It has a bunch of compartments and the construction of the bag is great.I don't know about the water resistance and durability yet, since I have not had it long, but it does seem well made and I'm not planning on being in the rain with it.It was well packaged when it arrived and came with a storage bag, which is a very nice bonus.I highly recommend this item. So many cute color combos! It was hard to choose just one.Post Trip UPDATE: I loved all of the pockets and compartments in this backpack and it's gorgeous. The only thing I didn't love was the top zipper of the main compartment and how, when full, it was very difficult to zip and not feel like I could be damaging the zipper. reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars The multi tool of backpacks.', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I bought this backpack for daily walks to a local gym and to mushroom hunt once in a while. The shoulder padding makes carrying heavy loads very comfortable and the handle on top has made picking up, attaching, and removing from my back a snap, it feels durable too. The straps around the belt and chest are adjustable to make it supportive while moving. I feel the value of this backpack is high, as it does everything I need and is durable.Edit: After just buying this backpack again, I noticed in one of the product photos showed a zippered pocket on the bottom of the backpack I never noticed while owning one for a long time, so now with winter approaching I am going to keep a small container of hand cream and lip balm… so HAPPY with this backpack!", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States November 23, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortably carry a TON of stuff & durable too', 'author': 'Rae(Skullsnroses)', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I took a week long trip for a festival & roughed it & slept outside. Its also durable being drug on & off multiple greyhounds & shoved into the space below my feet as well as roughing it outside sleeping i have no rips or tears & all my zippers & everything work perfectly. title: kasibon 15.6 inch Laptop Backpack for Women, Large Wide Top Open Travel Backpack Work Bag Water Resistant Anti Theft Backpack with Charging Port
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Brilliant Backpack!', 'author': 'Cattle Pillar', 'rating': 5, 'content': "This backpack is very sturdy and well made and I take it pretty much everywhere with me. I am a crocheter and the wife of a guy with cancer so I am always lugging projects with me to and fro appointments as well as paperwork and notebooks for note taking. This is not a huge backpack so I do have to keep some projects at home once they get too big (I make blankets mostly) but I have been able to start and work on several projects on the go since his diagnosis. Waiting for appointments can take forever and I hate wasting good crocheting time! It's perfect for crocheters and knitters because it opens at the top instead of from the side. It keeps my yarn organized because it's not spilling out all the time.The one thing that kind stinks about it is related to what makes it so awesome, the top opening. It is hard to get it zippered fast because you have to hold both sides together in order to zip it. When we are called back to appointments I usually end up having to hold it by the top straps instead of putting it on my back because I can't get my project back inside and get it zippered up fast enough. It's not a one handed operation for sure.The side pockets are great for water bottles (from the store, not my Yeti) and the front pouch is great for storing masks and granola bars. For me it's pretty perfect and looks good too.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States July 10, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Exceeds expectations', 'author': 'Kcat', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Bought this bag for multiple uses. Much. Space! I can fit an entire weekend\'s worth of clothing and toiletries for myself in the main pocket. (Just for a little context, I\'m 5\'0", and only wear leggings.) I can also fit my small chrome book in the laptop pocket, and my 17" gaming laptop in the large main part, plus all of the cords and accessories that go with them. I can also fit everything I need on a long flight, with room to spare!-Fits under the personal item standards for most airlines.-The plugin for charging banks is easily accessible and easy to use. You can use your own cord on the outside to charge your device. If you have a power bank that takes a different cord then what the bag comes with, its simple to slip it through instead.Cons:None that I have found!List of pockets:-2 water extendable water bottle pockets-1 zippered front pocket that has 2 smaller pockets, and a pen holder inside-1 smaller zippered pocket-A small zippered pocket on the back-In the large main pocket: -Laptop pocket -Tablet/notebook pocket -2 small pockets on the sides -2 small ones on the front -2 pen holders', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 3, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great sturdy bag!', 'author': 'Ash', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Bought this bag for work. reviews: [{'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars KROSER's Skies Above: A Pilot's Perfect Companion!", 'author': 'Gary C', 'rating': 5, 'content': "Navigating the intricate world of pilot training requires not only skill but also the right equipment - and KROSER's 17.3 Inch XL Travel Laptop Backpack delivers splendidly on that front. Yet, KROSER accommodates all of them with ease, ensuring I'm always prepared for my training sessions. No more leaving a vital piece of equipment or a crucial book behind!The Hard Shell Saferoom is another feature that deserves high praise. It adds an extra layer of protection for delicate items, ensuring they remain safe and secure. For someone like me, who values my gear, this feature is an absolute boon.Furthermore, the inclusion of an RFID pocket showcases the thought KROSER has put into modern-day needs. It's not just about carrying items but also ensuring security in a digital age.In terms of comfort, the backpack does not disappoint. Despite packing it to the brim, the ergonomically designed straps distribute weight evenly, ensuring I can move effortlessly from one session to another.To sum it up, KROSER's Travel Laptop Backpack is more than just a storage solution; it's a reliable partner in my journey through pilot training. If you're in search of a backpack that marries functionality with style and durability, look no further!", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States September 17, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent bag, I was surprised by the quality!', 'author': 'T. It’s ridiculously comfortable and I would buy another and recommend it to others.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 23, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Super High Quality', 'author': 'justsomeguy', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I know this thing is made is China and I hate that it is (Communists); but this thing is crazy good!! Storage compartments galore to store your PC, some clothes and anything else you can think of. Beefy zippers that look like they will last. Strong, attractive looking material. I have a couple buddies with $200 and $400 backpacks that brag about it but this backpack was probably made in the same building as they were by the same seamstresses. I looked for seam flaws. NONE. Superbly stitched. So if I am keeping one of those dear ladies employed, I’m okay with it. I might buy another so when in 10 years this fails, I have another one.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 15, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars not bad, not perfect', 'author': 'neminem', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I bought this backpack after a lot of deliberation, to replace a previous one from a different brand that I immediately disliked, and which started falling apart immediately as well. By comparison, this one is obviously much better (a low bar, but I do like it overall). The biggest issue is the laptop compartment itself, though - it fits my large laptop fine, and it does fit fairly snugly in the sleeve, making it easy to carry around with you, however the sleeve itself feels kinda flimsy, and it just barely fits around the top, too, so I\'d be a lot more worried about damaging it if it got dropped wrong, than I have been with some other laptop travel backpacks I\'ve used (sadly, my favorite one doesn\'t quite fit the new, slightly larger than 17.1 inch screen laptops they\'re making these days). Still better than nothing, though, obviously, and it\'d be fine on a plane, I\'m just a little more cautious when I get to the hotel and haven\'t unpacked yet. It\'s padded, just not *very* padded (and no padding for the top). Unfortunately, I didn\'t really see any that were much *more* padded, either. (At least none that still fit large laptops like mine - and this one does, if barely.)In terms of space, though, overall this wins. I do miss how my previous backpack had two decent sized "primary" compartments, the one with the laptop compartment, and another separate one, that were both pretty big. This one has the laptop compartment that\'s exactly the right size for a laptop, then one enormous compartment, and two much smaller ones. That\'s a pretty minor complaint, though. The smallest compartment has a pouch for a tablet (or just two separated spaces for your small items), the second, slightly larger smaller compartment has a bunch more separated small pouches inside (including one with an internal zipper). then the main compartment accordions out a big, so it can fit a decent sized package, or more clothing than you\'d expect from a backpack this size. But I\'ve also flown with it and not had a problem getting it under the seat. (Only the main compartment is particularly useful for filling with clothes, though. The other two are clearly designed more for pills, keys, paperbacks, small electronics, etc.)There are also two small zippered pockets on the side, and a third on the top. The one on the top contains a *removable* hard internal pouch for holding a pair of sunglasses - I was actually going to complain about it (it gets in the way, if you aren\'t using the space for sunglasses)... until I looked at it again just now, and yeah, completely removeable. (I use it for coins and things, since it\'s the easiest to access.) Each side also has a small outer mesh pouch, which looks like you\'d use it for holding things like water bottles, but I can\'t stress enough, they aren\'t large enough for full-sized water bottles to fit comfortably without falling out - my only other real complaint about the backpack. The main compartment does also have a space for plugging in a usb power bank (it doesn\'t *contain* one, you can just plug one in.) Then you can plug your own usb cable into the outside, and charge a phone that way. It\'s kind of a neat feature, though I don\'t really use it much. Works fine, though.It does fit comfortably on my back, with a decent amount of padding - we finally went on the Alaska cruise we booked in 2019, a couple months ago, I took it all over Alaska for a couple weeks, I can say, it\'s a lot more comfortable than my previous backpack. Feels a lot sturdier, too, though I haven\'t had it for a terribly long time, yet. I just wish I could find one like this, just slightly more padding for the laptop pouch. Overall, I\'m happy with it, though - way happier than my previous one, though admittedly that\'s a low bar.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 21, 2022', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars So much room!', 'author': 'P. Hasen', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I read a blog where a retired couple travelled after retirement for one year using a carry on and backpack each. Challenge on! We didn’t have any trouble with this amazing pack and we were both surprised how much room there was in each of them. TONS of room and so many pockets. I really like the zipper quality (main zippers are lockable), fabric quality, hardened sun/glasses built in case, sturdy handle with cabling, padded straps and back cushions, RFID pocket, secret hidden pocket, compression straps, water bottle pockets, computer/tablet padded envelope, and did I mention tons of room?! And fully packed, it fits under the seat of a max 737aircraft. And room for my feet. We look forward to more (and longer) trips with these packs. Well done Krosser! What I didn’t like about these packs? I don’t think so. We just got them so remembering where you put stuff in the beginning can be a challenge!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 15, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars This thing is great', 'author': 'hoof_hearted4', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I use this thing as my tech pack. holds my laptop and such if I need to go into the office, holds chargers and battery packs for my kids sporting events.
