Shull', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I was searching for a bag to carry my small APS-C kit so I could always have a camera with me. Most other sling bags I looked at were either too large (fit full frame or too many lenses) or too small and would not fit a Sony a6700 with a lens attached. This bag can fit the a6700 with a lens attached and several accessories. Note that it will not fit a full frame camera with a lens attached in any orientation, though one will fit without a lens attached and the lens stored next to it.Shown in the pictures are my primary kit of the a6700 with the 24mm f2.8G attached and the 50mm f1.8 OSS. Beneath the divider shelf is a Peak Design Slide strap. It will even fit the camera with the 70-350 G attached. Not shown are the microfiber cloth, UV filter, and spare SD card in the interior zippered pocket. Closing the bag was difficult at first, but the material stretched slightly after leaving everything in the bag overnight and now it is a perfect fit.My only minor complaint is that the strap was not removable and also not easily adjustable. Since my use case was to have a bag I could grab and throw in the car or carry as a sling bag, I decided to cut off the strap and add the Peak Design anchors. This way I can use the Slide strap to either carry the bag and quickly adjust it to fit, or use the strap on the camera based on my needs at the moment.Materials are pretty good and fit and finish is good. I expect it to be durable and long lasting. I believe I have found the perfect grab and go bag for a minimalist kit.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 20, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent, affordable sling bag.', 'author': 'Eric Hardt', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I favor this sling bag over much more expensive competitor's bags.The surface of this bag is non-abrasive on my shirts!Despite its affordability, the bag doesn't feel cheap.The bag and compartment zippers induce confidence that wearing it in the rain will protect the gear.It is slim and therefore doesn't look bulky, yet it fits comfortably a Sony A7RIII with a Sony 35mm GM lens and has room for another lens, mobile phone and spare batteries.The cushioning of the bag seems sufficient enough to protect the gear.Besides the two outside compartments, there is another compartment with a magnetic closure, e.g: Passport and airplane tickets.I can recommend this bag, especially for travel, if you don't want to haul too much photo equipment with you.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 2, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Really like this bag', 'author': 'Vmw', 'rating': 5, 'content': "After buying several bags, I finally found this one that works very well for me. It's not too big or too small. It fits my Sony RX 10 with 600mm lens without being cramped and has plenty room left over for my filters, charger, cords, and spare batteries. My camera does not use extra lenses, but if someone needed to, an extra lens would fit. The inside is thoughtfully designed with a zippered pocket for batteries and a couple of other pockets. title: ULANZI BP10 Hardshell Camera Backpack, Professional Waterproof Photography Camera Case Anti Theft Travel for Photographers Unisex Drone DSLR Mirrorless Camera Lens Tripod Holder 17'' Laptop Black 35L
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Finally! An affordable quality bag for my gear!', 'author': 'Christopher', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I\'ve been looking for a bag that\'s not ridiculously overpriced, that\'s durable, and has room for more gear than I usually carry. I\'m easily able to fit a 5D Mark IV with a 70-200 2.8 II attached, a 6D Mark II with a 24-70 2.8 II attached, a 100mm 2.8 L Macro, a 50mm 1.8, 24-105 F4 II, 35mm 1.4 II, 16-35mm F4 inside, and my Godox V860 III fits in the front pouch with room to spare. I haven\'t even expanded the bag to gain its additional 10L of space, but that\'ll come in handy for traveling when I need to pack clothes and other essentials. There are also a ton of pockets for memory cards, card readers, batteries, etc. All for under $150 USD. The outer materials of the bag are soft but durable, and the fabrics inside are all soft to the touch but well made. The velcro tabs are also easy to configure how I need them, and I still have a couple of pieces left over. The belt attachment that comes with the bag fits me, even though I\'m a big guy (6\'4" and 365lbs).I don\'t often travel with this much gear, but I have an out of state wedding I\'m going to be photographing in April and I needed a bag that fits extra gear, and can be taken as a carry on. Overall, VERY impressed with this new bag. This is also my first purchase of a Ulanzi product, so I\'ll have to check some of their other stuff out now as well. With everything I have loaded so far, the total weight of the bag is at 22.7 lbs.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 31, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Everything but the kitchen sink fits.', 'author': 'gail duckworth', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'In preparation for an African Safari coming up in June, I found myself in need of a larger camera backpack. It seems to be very well made, has plenty of room for all my gear, is comfortable on my back, and most importantly there is a zippered access panel on both sides. Although I have only had this backpack for a week, as of right now, I have no complaints and would definitely recommend it.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '2.0 out of 5 stars Zippers do not hold up', 'author': 'Jordan Johnson', 'rating': 2, 'content': 'Zippers are not built to last. Coming from a langly bag that has very sturdy zippers I was shocked. You will be replacing them in 2 years be warned!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': False}, {'title': "4.0 out of 5 stars It's a very well designed bag but has a flaw I don't think it will last years of hard use.", 'author': 'Jimmy Ji', 'rating': 4, 'content': "This bag is hard to fully recommend, but I don't think it's a bad bag.I love the look and design and all the compartments and pockets are amazing.It uses it's space really well and has more pockets than most other bags if that is important to you.The expansion from 25l to 35l is cool but also a problem since you sacrifice that extra 10l as a separate compartment instead of in the main compartment. So the depth of where you will put your camera and lenses could be deeper if it wasn't split into 2 compartments but you actually don't have that much as you would think. I am using small/medium lenses in my photos. Something like a 24-105 would not be flush with the main compartment. (But you could still zip it up)I thought I could live with the PU leather, but if you are like me and throw your bag around then I do not think the material will last.What I hate the most about this bag is that you have to open it face down backup so that means the front is on whatever the ground surface is. I wish there was at least another hard cover on the other front pouch to take the damage and force , but since there isn't I can see the front bottom pouch getting shredded over time.Also the fact you have to open the main compartment with the front down mean you have to keep zipping it up to then flip back around to get to the front pockets. This bag slowed me down on a recent shoot a lotlIf you swing the backpack around to the front to grab the camera on one of the side zippers that go to the main compartment the camera will be upside down because of that reason that it has to open face down.I love the included waist strap that you can attach or take off. I had to tuck the clip straps underneath the pockets since I did not want it dangling and honestly it works great. Not sure if it was designed for that.I can recommend this if you don't think you will abuse your backpack, but I am so run and gun the backpack will get pushed to it's limits though I think $150 is a bit high.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 20, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': 'se ve muy bien', 'author': 'javier', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'apenas la usare pero se ve de muy buena calidad, estaba buscanbdo una mochila asi desde hace tiempo y otras de 2500 o menos se rompian facil por el peso que cargo en la mochila pero esta s eve que resistira mucho y es muy amplia', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in Mexico January 5, 2024', 'is_verified': True}]

reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, stain resistant, fits all my stuff. 👍', 'author': 'Kate', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I am a student in photography and art. I’m also disabled and chronically ill. Ergo, my bag has to carry a LOT of stuff — spare masks, medication, powdered electrolytes, camera lenses, water bottles, snacks, textbooks, art supplies, noise canceling headphones, spare film, DnD stuff, and other items. Sometimes my folding cane as well. So I wanted a school bag that didn’t feel like a freshman backpack that could store the kitchen sink.I ended up ordering two bags, one of these and one from a different brand. Despite being a little cheaper than the other brand, the quality is MUCH higher on this bag. I love it. It’s incredibly sturdy and stain resistant (getting it in navy blue didn’t hurt in that regard). There’s a gazillion pockets so everything has a home. I use the little zipper bag for little odds and ends I need easy access to like Liquid IV, emergency meds, antibacterial wipes, microfibers, etc. In spite of everything I shove in there, there’s still enough room for my binders, textbooks, laptop, etc. When I’m all loaded down and carrying on both shoulders, the weight distribution is comfortable and even, and it doesn’t interfere with me using my cane.It’s also just a beautiful bag. I really like the design choices. There’s an internal bar in the top of the backpack underneath the zipper to help keep its form. It opens like a coin purse and makes loading and unloading very easy. The details are well designed and implemented. I think others have had zipper issues but I have not.The big front flap does not have a zipper. It’s just the flap down holding it in place. I imagine it would be very easy for someone to reach in and steal from you. I am not in crowds or other environments that invite pickpockets, so this isn’t an issue for me. Also there’s a zippered pocket under the straps (protected by your back when you’re carrying it) for cash/cards, but I think it would be very uncomfortable to carry your entire wallet in there.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States October 7, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars The Bag Is Amazing -- The Clutch, not so much', 'author': 'Emma', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'This bag is better than the product photos... I don\'t know why I need this many pockets but hopefully it prevents the graveyard of junk that ends up at the bottom of all my bags. I had a similar bag to this that I always struggled with the flip top to access items inside.The small clutch that comes with it is the only thing I really don\'t care for -- It might be good for a small makeup holder, maybe a first aid kit/feminine hygiene kit, potentially diabetic supplies; but, in comparison to the bag, it\'s just feels like an after thought. I think it\'s fine as a little freebie kind of thing but it\'s not anything AMAZING.Please note: I am an Amazon Vine Reviewer but I was not sponsored to review this item 😊.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 12, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars It's perfect for travel", 'author': 'J. The striped lining is super cute too, and makes finding things inside much easier than if it were a dark color.It has a bunch of compartments and the construction of the bag is great.I don't know about the water resistance and durability yet, since I have not had it long, but it does seem well made and I'm not planning on being in the rain with it.It was well packaged when it arrived and came with a storage bag, which is a very nice bonus.I highly recommend this item. title: Laptop Backpack for Women Travel Canvas Backpack for Women Vintage Green Aesthetic Backpack for School
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite bag so far..!', 'author': 'Gabriella', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I really like the color, a "calm green" without being light neon or dark army green, just right in the middle- almost like a blue/green which is perfect..It fits everything without looking or feeling too bulky, when usually other bags I\'ve tried are way more bulky or uncomfortable..I\'m kind of a "minimalist prepper", meaning I like to be prepared, but I don\'t like tons of baggage or huge bags to have to lug around like most preppers/survivalists..(And in a real survival situation, the last thing you want is your survival bag to be the same thing that\'s going to drain your energy, just from carrying it when you fill it too much...)So I\'ve been hunting for the right bag for years, and this one is the best one I\'ve found so far..!This bag has 3 compartments, which I found is the perfect number- main one for your normal things (like journals, books, tablet, pens, portable charger, etc), then a middle pocket that fits first aid (trauma supplies, bandaids, hygene products, medicine, hand sanitizer, etc) and then an outside pocket that fits protein bars and high calorie food, to keep you full and keep you going..! (Whether for a regular day, or for fighting zombies, it works both ways..!)Side pockets fit my 20oz waters perfectly, and I love how they have the elastic to stretch a little and hold the bottle as needed too.This is actually the perfect BugOut Bag (meaning the bag you take when you need to evacuate for natural disasters, etc), only I like to carry my bugout bag as my EDC bag, so I always have everything with me for whoever needs something... (Or even an alien invasion.. 👽😉)I love the overall feel of the bag; it has some structure without being too "stiff", but not too "flimsy" where it won\'t stand on its own either- just a more "relaxed" design...Zippers suck a little bit, on a scale of 1-10 they\'d probably be a 7 because they don\'t glide that smooth, but it\'s not that big a deal either; you just usually need both hands to unzip instead of being able to use one hand..The inside pockets in the main compartment do seem a little flimsy, and shoulder straps are not the best for alleviating pressure, but compared to the overall bag and the price you get for it, I would take this bag over a $100 "fancy bag" any day...It has a cute and "rustic" look to it, meaning it\'s good to take anywhere, and it\'s still functional too. (I hate bags that are just for show, like "sparkles", and don\'t have any functionality to them...)I also love how this brand doesn\'t care about plastering their name on the bag; because I don\'t like to buy stuff that makes me a "walking advertisement"...(I included pics with and without flash to give better perception of bag\'s color.)All the pictures shown are with everything inside the bag, and as you can see it\'s spaced out pretty well so it doesn\'t look "overstuffed", and it still just looks like a normal sized backpack...(Mine isn\'t even too heavy with all this in it, because I have small amounts of everything, so it\'s maybe 10-15 pounds and that\'s it..)', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States June 18, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great Urban Day Pack', 'author': 'A Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': '1. AestheticsWonderful sturdy green canvas with canvas straps. The lining is golden brown soft nylon of some kind. See note under "Caveats" below.2. Outside PocketsCan fit a 32 ounce metal water bottle on one side, a slimmer bottle on the other secured with an elastic strap. Outside zipper pocket is large enough for snacks, pens, phone and so on. A second deeper zipper pocket could be used for a scarf, gloves, or small packed lunch.3. Inside PocketsGoing from the portion that sits against your back toward the outside, there\'s a small zipper compartment for a small wallet, iPods, or small items. Below it is a deep wide pocket that works well for tablets, 13" laptops, and regular sized books. There\'s no elastic here, so whatever you put in will fit loosely and may bounce around a bit (your own laptop sleeve might be a good idea). reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars well made bag', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I love all of the pockets and storage areas in this bag. The color will look great with anything and looks like it will wipe free of stains. I also appreciate the waterproofness of the bag and the fact that it will make a great carry on for my upcoming trip. Large enough to carry everything I will need enroute and more and also to comply with TSA restrictions. I really like the bottom pocket into which a pair of shoes with sox tucked inside will fit without getting my other clothing soiled. Opens wide you so have good access to all of your belongings. It is also very well made. You will not regret getting this bag!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 10, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars Nice personal item for air travel - just don't over stuff it", 'author': 'G. Eliot', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I purchased this backpack specifically to use as a "personal item" for a domestic flight on an airline (Frontier) that charges for any type of bag other than personal items. I bought the size "large," thinking that it was slightly under their size requirements for a personal item, so it should be good. I then proceeded to pack it full for my few-day trip. The airline now requires all personal items (at least out of Denver) to be placed into their sizing scale to ensure it will fit before allowing boarding. I managed to cram the bag into their mechanism, but it was not easy, so just be forewarned if you are one to like to stuff things full that you may struggle with this.Beyond the issue specific to this airline, the backpack itself was mostly great for traveling! It\'s water resistant, has lots of compartments/zippers/etc and has a padded back to provide some comfort while carrying. I particularly like the separate compartment for shoes, and although anything added here does take up space inside the interior of the bag, I like not having dirty shoes touching my clean clothing or getting electronics wet. I will say it\'s easy to pack this bag which is both a blessing and curse as I ended up having a pretty heavy bag to carry -- of course, that is the fault of the packer and not the bag itself.The small front zipper was great for keeping my phone and ID handy for showing as needed, and I appreciate the compression straps/clasps to help keep the pack as small as possible.I should also note that it would likely be a struggle to get this item under many airline seats (which is often the requirement for a personal item), even if it wasn\'t stuffed full. I didn\'t even try because there was plenty of overhead room, but another possible hiccup for travel.Although I\'ve only used this for one round trip, it seems as though it will hold up decently to use and hopefully, in the future, I won\'t have to put quite so much into it so it won\'t be as hefty a load to carry. For the price and ease of use, I\'d absolutely recommend and/or purchase again if needed in the future, but hoping this one will last awhile as I don\'t deal with a ton of airline traveling.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States June 12, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Tons of pockets and little compartments! Durable and reliable.', 'author': 'Cams', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'TL;DR: Lots of pockets, durable, cute colors. Overall a good buy! It also survived a round in my washing machine so, bonus points for that.I took some time to use this bag for a couple of months before writing any kind of review and it has passed what I considered enough trials and tribulations.There are a plethora of pockets to help organize your belongings and to facilitate access; there\'s even a "waterproof" one that helps provide peace of mind in the event you\'re worried something will leak. There\'s a "secret" pocket on the backside for important things you don\'t want people accessing easily. The only pockets I really have qualms with is the "shoe" compartment at the bottom, since it doesn\'t really provide extra space. It uses the same internal space as everything in the bag since the pocket juts inward rather than outward. And the second one is the water bottle pocket, because it doesn\'t expand very much and it\'s a bit shallow but it fits 16 oz water bottles nicely. A little more wary about 24 oz bottles.There exists an attachment on the bag where you can attach a cable to the inside of your bag and run it to the outside to help you charge your device on the go. They\'ve included a USB-A to USB-A cable, but as I said, it can be unhooked and replaced with whichever type of cable you need.This bag also has buckles to help keep all your stuff compact and from jostling around.This is a great, durable bag that has weathered carrying ALL of my belongings (clothes, toiletries, souvenirs, etc) for a 6 day trip to Hawaii and also survived being lugged around and stuffed after a week long excursion to Italy for the same purpose, in addition to other smaller trips I\'ve taken.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States October 2, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Great for Travel', 'author': 'KMH', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I originally got this backpack with the intention of using it to my college classes, but it was a little too big for that. I can fit a lot more stuff than I thought, and the laptop sleeve and suitcase strap are both very handy. Overall, this is a great value for the price.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 19, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars A Must-Have for Travel', 'author': 'Mandi in VA', 'rating': 5, 'content': "This came with me on a 3+ week international travel stint and I will not travel again without it. The zippered sections were just right, and the zippers line up to be able to use TSA/travel locks. the straps are very, very comfortable, and the bag is sturdy and durable yet soft and comfy to wear for extended periods. I loved the color, almost periwinkle, but if I were to buy this bag again I'd get a darker color to better withstand the inevitable dirt/marks from air/car/bus travel. This bag kept clothes, a blanket, money, electronics, and everything dry in rainy Ireland, snowy Germany, and a few downpours in Italy. There is a strap on the back that was perfect for the handle of my wheeled carry-on, and the weight distribution was such that the entire set-up didn't tip over. I would almost call this bag indispensable!", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 23, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars easy to carry carry-on', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I wanted a backpack that could double as a carry-on that was also affordable and I was really happy with this. The backpack fits the standard as a carry-on for Turkish Airlines and fits in the overhead compartment in all the charter/tour buses I was taking. I was able to fit my clunky Hokas and some bags of candy that I got in the Duty-Free shop in the bottom shoe compartment and the "luggage" mid-section of the bag had enough for two light changes of clothes that I put in a small pouch from my packing cube set. It also fit my sunglasses, regular glasses, and my quart bag which was full of my liquids. What shoes or if you put shoes in that bottom compartment determines how much space for clothes you have but I was happy with being able to carry two changes of clothes on a 23 hr+ travel day. I was also able to fit my MacBook Air and laptop case and Kindle with all my wires and chargers in the back laptop compartment. The two pockets in the front are surprisingly spacious. The wet pocket goes deep since it has no pockets and some snacks got lost in there because of how big it is, but it was nice that they fit - Don\'t forget about the snacks you chuck in there. I would recommend it if you are taking it on a quick overnight trip or as a carry-on bag complementing your full-size luggage for a longer trip. The space inside with all the different pockets and storage areas is perfect for that busy work day or for the typical college student as well. There is plenty of room for your laptop, wireless mouse, USB Hub, chargers, tablet, file folders, or anything else that someone in business may take with them on a daily basis. The laptop area of the backpack in specific, has a really nice padded area for added protection for your laptop. It also has a strap to secure your laptop in the designated pocket for additional protection. The main compartment that houses your laptop also has additional pockets inside so you have plenty of storage for everything you would need. The front zipper pocket has many different compartments as well, for pens, a stylus, highlighters, business cards, or anything else that you would want quick access to during your work day or school day.Another nice feature of this backpack is the included USB Charging Port and Headphone Jack. Then on the outside, you can plug in your USB charger cord and charge your phone throughout the day directly from your backpack. You can also place your phone inside your backpack and plug the provided 3mm headphone cord into your phone, then on the outside of your backpack you can plug in your headphones to the provided port and listen to music without having to hold your phone on you, this is especially nice if you are in a crowded area and do not want to risk theft of your device.The built in combination lock is a 3 digit combination style lock. The provided instructions are easy to follow for you to setup your own combination code. I have vigorously tested the lock, and it truly does seem to be really durable and would take a bit for your average thief to get into. It also gives you that 'deterrent' so that a thief won't even want to attempt to steal anything from your backpack because of the lock that is in place.In summary, if you are looking for a stylish and secured backpack to use for your business needs or for that typical college or even high school student, then look no further.
